{"type":"text","timestamp":1775839848285,"sessionID":"ses_287b2baffffecGB2s9iHjnUgJY","part":{"id":"prt_d784da2b50016xHAJB8o6kdnKf","messageID":"msg_d784d9628001cBi9cavPr2Xiv2","sessionID":"ses_287b2baffffecGB2s9iHjnUgJY","type":"text","text":"Now I understand the structure. I need to write a delta-spec.md for AR-002 (CodeInterpreter CRD type definition) following the OpenSpec format with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios, similar to the existing AR-001 document.","time":{"start":1775839848282,"end":1775839848282}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839921280,"sessionID":"ses_287b2baffffecGB2s9iHjnUgJY","part":{"id":"prt_d784da75c001CI5hnP1x2Zg2VY","messageID":"msg_d784d9628001cBi9cavPr2Xiv2","sessionID":"ses_287b2baffffecGB2s9iHjnUgJY","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_2d8afbb28ca94f28a6cb7dce","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","content":"# AR-002 — CRD CodeInterpreter 类型定义 Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the CodeInterpreter CRD type implementation including Go API types, validation, CRD manifests, client-go library, informers, and listers for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter API type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go` with `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterSpec` types. `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL include `runtimeRef` (string), `code` (string), `language` (string), `executionPolicy` (ExecutionPolicy), and `resources` (ResourceQuota). `CodeInterpreter` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type registration\n\n- **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&CodeInterpreter{}, &CodeInterpreterList{})` is called during init\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be registered in the scheme with `Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`, `APIVersion = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Runtime reference binding\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter YAML with `spec.runtimeRef: \"python-3.11\"`\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed by the scheme\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.RuntimeRef` SHALL be populated with the runtime name string\n\n#### Scenario: Code field parsing\n\n- **GIVEN** `spec.code` contains Python code string\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is deserialized\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Code` SHALL contain the exact code string\n\n#### Scenario: Language specification\n\n- **GIVEN** `spec.language: \"python\"` or `spec.language: \"go\"`\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Language` SHALL be populated with the language identifier\n\n#### Scenario: Execution policy configuration\n\n- **GIVEN** `spec.executionPolicy` with `timeout: \"30s\"` and `maxRetries: 3`\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed\n- **THEN** `ExecutionPolicy.Timeout` (metav1.Duration) and `ExecutionPolicy.MaxRetries` (int32) SHALL be populated\n\n#### Scenario: Resource quota binding\n\n- **GIVEN** `spec.resources` specifies `cpu: \"500m\"`, `memory: \"512Mi\"`, `storage: \"1Gi\"`\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is validated by the scheme\n- **THEN** `Resources` SHALL be of type `ResourceQuota` with parsed values\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter status subresource\n\nThe system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterStatus` with `Phase` (CodeInterpreterPhase), `Conditions` ([]CodeInterpreterCondition), `Result` (string), `ExecutionTime` (metav1.Duration), and `LastTransitionTime` (metav1.Time). `CodeInterpreter` SHALL expose `.status` via the status subresource.\n\n#### Scenario: Status phase transitions\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `status.phase = \"Pending\"`\n- **WHEN** the controller updates status to `\"Running\"` then to `\"Succeeded\"`\n- **THEN** `LastTransitionTime` SHALL be updated for each transition and Conditions appended\n\n#### Scenario: Condition management\n\n- **GIVEN** a condition of type `\"Ready\"` with `status: \"True\"`, `reason: \"ExecutionComplete\"`, `message: \"Code executed successfully\"`\n- **WHEN** status is updated via the status subresource\n- **THEN** the condition SHALL be upserted into `status.conditions` with `lastTransitionTime` set\n\n#### Scenario: Execution result storage\n\n- **GIVEN** code execution completes with output\n- **WHEN** the controller sets `status.result` to the execution output\n- **THEN** `status.result` SHALL contain the stdout/stderr of code execution\n\n#### Scenario: Execution time tracking\n\n- **GIVEN** code execution takes 5.2 seconds\n- **WHEN** the controller updates `status.executionTime`\n- **THEN** `status.executionTime.Duration` SHALL be `5.2s`\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter phase and condition types\n\nThe system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterPhase` constants: `Pending`, `Running`, `Succeeded`, `Failed`, `Terminating`. The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreterConditionType` constants: `Ready`, `Executing`, `Completed`.\n\n#### Scenario: Phase constant availability\n\n- **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterPhaseRunning` is referenced\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"Running\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Condition type constant availability\n\n- **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `CodeInterpreterConditionReady` is referenced\n- **THEN** it SHALL equal `\"Ready\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Condition structure\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterCondition` is created\n- **WHEN** fields are set: `Type`, `Status`, `Reason`, `Message`, `LastTransitionTime`\n- **THEN** the condition SHALL match the structure of `AgentRuntimeCondition`\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter validation\n\nThe system SHALL implement `ValidateCodeInterpreter(obj *CodeInterpreter) field.ErrorList` in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go`. Validation SHALL check: `runtimeRef` is non-empty, `code` is non-empty, `language` is valid (python, go, nodejs), `resources` are valid quantities.\n\n#### Scenario: Valid CodeInterpreter validation\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `runtimeRef: \"python-3.11\"`, `code: \"print('hello')\"`, `language: \"python\"`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n- **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL be empty\n\n#### Scenario: Missing runtimeRef validation\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `runtimeRef`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n- **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.runtimeRef` with reason `Required`\n\n#### Scenario: Missing code validation\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `code`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n- **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.code` with reason `Required`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid language validation\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `language: \"invalid\"`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n- **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.language` with reason `NotSupported`\n\n#### Scenario: Invalid resource quantity validation\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `resources.cpu: \"invalid\"`\n- **WHEN** `ValidateCodeInterpreter` is called\n- **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain an error for `spec.resources.cpu` with reason `Invalid`\n\n#### Scenario: Status update phase transition validation\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `status.phase = \"Succeeded\"`\n- **WHEN** controller attempts to update phase to `\"Running\"` via `ValidateCodeInterpreterStatusUpdate`\n- **THEN** `field.ErrorList` SHALL contain a `Forbidden` error for invalid phase transition\n\n### Requirement: CRD manifest generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate `manifests/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` via `make gen-crd` using controller-gen.\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD with status subresource\n\n- **GIVEN** `+genclient` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers on `CodeInterpreter`\n- **WHEN** `make gen-crd` runs controller-gen\n- **THEN** the CRD manifest SHALL include `spec.subresources.status: {}`\n\n#### Scenario: CRD schema validation for required fields\n\n- **GIVEN** `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` markers on `runtimeRef` and `code`\n- **WHEN** CRDs are generated\n- **THEN** the OpenAPI v3 schema SHALL mark `runtimeRef` and `code` as required\n\n#### Scenario: CRD group and version\n\n- **GIVEN** `SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n- **WHEN** CRDs render\n- **THEN** `metadata.name` SHALL be `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` and `spec.group = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`\n\n#### Scenario: CRD printer columns\n\n- **GIVEN** `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` markers on `CodeInterpreter`\n- **WHEN** CRDs are generated\n- **THEN** the CRD SHALL include printer columns for NAME, PHASE, RUNTIME, and AGE\n\n### Requirement: client-go typed client for CodeInterpreter\n\nThe system SHALL generate typed client under `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `CodeInterpreterInterface` providing `Create`, `Update`, `UpdateStatus`, `Delete`, `Get`, `List`, `Watch`, `Patch` methods.\n\n#### Scenario: Create CodeInterpreter via typed client\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured `Clientset` and valid `CodeInterpreter` object\n- **WHEN** `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Create(ctx, ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be created via the K8s API and returned with populated metadata\n\n#### Scenario: Update status via typed client\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter with a mutable status\n- **WHEN** `UpdateStatus(ctx, ci, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** only the status subresource SHALL be updated\n\n#### Scenario: List with label selector\n\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters with labels `app=runner` in namespace `default`\n- **WHEN** `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=runner\"})` is called\n- **THEN** only matching CodeInterpreters SHALL be returned\n\n#### Scenario: Watch for changes\n\n- **GIVEN** a watch on `CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n- **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created or updated\n- **THEN** the watch channel SHALL receive an `Event` with `Type` and `Object`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete by name\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `exec-1` exists\n- **WHEN** `Delete(ctx, \"exec-1\", metav1.DeleteOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from the API server\n\n#### Scenario: Patch update\n\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter\n- **WHEN** `Patch(ctx, \"exec-1\", types.MergePatchType, data, metav1.PatchOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be partially updated with patch data\n\n### Requirement: Informer factory for CodeInterpreter\n\nThe system SHALL generate informer under `client-go/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `CodeInterpreterInformer` and methods `Informer()`, `Lister()`, `NewCodeInterpreterInformer`, `NewFilteredCodeInterpreterInformer`.\n\n#### Scenario: Start informer for CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** a configured `SharedInformerFactory`\n- **WHEN** `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters().Informer()` is called and `factory.Start(stopCh)` runs\n- **THEN** the informer SHALL list-watch `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and populate its cache\n\n#### Scenario: Event handlers for CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer with `AddEventHandler` registered\n- **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created\n- **THEN** the `OnAdd` callback SHALL be invoked with the new object\n\n#### Scenario: Namespace-filtered informer\n\n- **GIVEN** `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` with namespace `production`\n- **WHEN** the factory starts\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter informer SHALL only watch CodeInterpreters in `production` namespace\n\n#### Scenario: Lister access from informer\n\n- **GIVEN** a synced CodeInterpreter informer\n- **WHEN** `informer.Lister().Get(\"exec-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned from the local cache\n\n### Requirement: Lister for CodeInterpreter\n\nThe system SHALL generate `CodeInterpreterLister` and `CodeInterpreterNamespaceLister` under `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter.go` with `List(selector)` and `Get(name)` methods.\n\n#### Scenario: List all CodeInterpreters\n\n- **GIVEN** a populated informer cache\n- **WHEN** `lister.List(labels.Everything())` is called\n- **THEN** all CodeInterpreters SHALL be returned from the cache\n\n#### Scenario: Get by name and namespace\n\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter named `exec-1` in namespace `default` exists in cache\n- **WHEN** `lister.CodeInterpreters(\"default\").Get(\"exec-1\")` is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned or `NotFound` error if absent\n\n#### Scenario: List with label filter\n\n- **GIVEN** CodeInterpreters with various labels in cache\n- **WHEN** `lister.List(labels.SelectorFromSet(labels.Set{\"type\": \"batch\"}))` is called\n- **THEN** only CodeInterpreters matching the label selector SHALL be returned\n\n### Requirement: Fake clients for CodeInterpreter testing\n\nThe system SHALL generate fake clients under `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/fake_codeinterpreter.go` implementing `CodeInterpreterInterface` for unit testing.\n\n#### Scenario: Unit test with fake client\n\n- **GIVEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset()` is called\n- **WHEN** `Create`, `Get`, `Update`, `Delete` are called on `fake.CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n- **THEN** operations SHALL succeed in-memory without contacting K8s API\n\n#### Scenario: Reactor for error injection\n\n- **GIVEN** a fake client with `PrependReactor(\"create\", \"codeinterpreters\", ...)` that returns an error\n- **WHEN** `Create` is called on `CodeInterpreters(\"default\")`\n- **THEN** the reactor SHALL intercept and return the injected error\n\n#### Scenario: Fake client pre-population\n\n- **GIVEN** a fake client created with `NewSimpleClientset(&existingCodeInterpreter)`\n- **WHEN** `Get(ctx, \"exec-1\", metav1.GetOptions{})` is called\n- **THEN** the pre-populated CodeInterpreter SHALL be returned\n\n### Requirement: Deepcopy generation for CodeInterpreter\n\nThe system SHALL generate `DeepCopy`, `DeepCopyInto`, `DeepCopyObject` methods for `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterList` in `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` via `make gen-deepcopy`.\n\n#### Scenario: DeepCopy for CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` object with populated spec and status\n- **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called\n- **THEN** a new `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be returned with all fields deeply copied\n\n#### Scenario: DeepCopy for CodeInterpreterSpec\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreterSpec` with nested `ExecutionPolicy` and `ResourceQuota`\n- **WHEN** `DeepCopy()` is called\n- **THEN** all nested pointers SHALL be newly allocated\n\n#### Scenario: DeepCopyObject for runtime.Object interface\n\n- **GIVEN** a `CodeInterpreter` used as `runtime.Object`\n- **WHEN** `DeepCopyObject()` is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return `runtime.Object` with a deep copy of the CodeInterpreter\n\n### Requirement: Expansion interfaces for CodeInterpreter\n\nThe system SHALL generate empty expansion interfaces `CodeInterpreterExpansion` in `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/generated_expansion.go` and `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion` in `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/expansion_generated.go`.\n\n#### Scenario: Client expansion interface\n\n- **GIVEN** the generated `CodeInterpreterExpansion` interface\n- **WHEN** a developer extends it with custom methods\n- **THEN** custom methods SHALL be available on `CodeInterpreterInterface` without regeneration\n\n#### Scenario: Lister expansion interface\n\n- **GIVEN** the generated `CodeInterpreterListerExpansion` interface\n- **WHEN** a developer extends it with custom lister methods\n- **THEN** custom methods SHALL be available on `CodeInterpreterLister` without regeneration\n\n### Requirement: Scheme and codec registration for CodeInterpreter\n\nThe system SHALL register CodeInterpreter types in `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` with `AddToScheme` functions for the generated client.\n\n#### Scenario: Scheme registration at client init\n\n- **GIVEN** the `client-go` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `scheme.AddToScheme(runtimeScheme)` is called\n- **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterList` types SHALL be recognizable by the scheme\n\n#### Scenario: Negotiated serializer for CodeInterpreter\n\n- **GIVEN** a REST client with `NegotiatedSerializer`\n- **WHEN** encoding/decoding is needed for CodeInterpreter\n- **THEN** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` SHALL be supported with `application/json`\n\n### Requirement: CodeInterpreter resource plural\n\nThe system SHALL use `codeinterpreters` as the REST resource plural for CodeInterpreter in client-go generated code.\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plural in typed client\n\n- **GIVEN** the generated `codeinterpreter.go` typed client\n- **WHEN** the REST client is configured\n- **THEN** `Resource(\"codeinterpreters\")` SHALL be used for API path construction\n\n#### Scenario: Resource plural in lister\n\n- **GIVEN** the generated `codeinterpreter.go` lister\n- **WHEN** `NewCodeInterpreterLister` is called\n- **THEN** it SHALL use `Resource(\"codeinterpreter\").GroupResource()` for the lister\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":211,"character":2},"end":{"line":216,"character":3}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#slicescontains"},"source":"slicescontains","message":"Loop can be simplified using slices.Contains"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":31,"character":1},"end":{"line":31,"character":19}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"var \"localSchemeBuilder\" is unused","tags":[1]}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775839921237,"end":1775839921275}}}}
